  "prompt": "What are some examples of cardiac muscles?",
  "response": "Cardiac muscles are specialized muscle tissues found in the heart that enable it to pump blood effectively throughout the body. The heart is composed of three main types of cardiac muscle cells:\n\n1. **Cardiomyocytes**: These are the main type of cardiac muscle cells, responsible for the contraction of the heart. They are connected by intercalated discs, which allow for coordinated contractions.\n\n2. **Pacemaker Cells**: Located in the sinoatrial (SA) node and the atrioventricular (AV) node, these cells generate electrical impulses that regulate the heartbeat.\n\n3. **Purkinje Fibers**: These specialized cells conduct electrical impulses rapidly through the ventricles, ensuring coordinated ventricular contraction.\n\nThese different types of cardiac muscle cells work together to ensure the heart functions efficiently as a pump.",
